Importing numpy:
    import numpy as np

Arrays in Numpy are Vectors and Matrices
VECTORS  - 1D Arrays
MATRICES - 2D Arrays

row    - number of subarrays
column - elements in each subarray

---------------------------------------------- BASIC FUNCTIONS ---------------------------------------------

Converting a Python List into Numpy Array:
    np.array(<python-list>)

Get an array(list) of range of numbers:
    np.arange(start, end, step)

Get an array of zeroes:
    VECTOR  - np.zeros(length)
    MATRICE - np.zeros((row, column))

Get an array of ones:
    VECTOR  - np.ones(length)
    MATRICE - np.ones((row, column))

Get an array(vector) of linearly spaced numbers:
    np.linspace(start, end, count)

Get an identity array(matrice):
    np.eye(size)

Generate a Random Array:
    Gaussian Randomness:
        VECTOR  - np.random.rand(length)
        MATRICE - np.random.rand(row, column)
    Normal Randomness:
        VECTOR  - np.random.randn(length)
        MATRICE - np.random.randn(row, column)
    Integers in Range:
        VECTOR - np.random.randint(start, end, length)

Reshape an Array:
    arr.reshape(row,column)

Find max/min of an Array:
    arr.min()
    arr.max()

Find location of max/min of an Array;
    arr.argmin()
    arr.argmax()

Know the shape of an Array:
    arr.shape()

Indexing is same as that of normal lists in Python, with the following addition:
    arr[1][2] == arr[1,2]
    arr[:2, 1:] (For subscripting an array)

Conditional Array:
    arr[cond]
        example - arr[arr>3]
    
---------------------------------------------- OPERATIONS ---------------------------------------------

Array with array operations:
    arr + arr   arr - arr   arr * arr   arr / arr

Scalar operations on array:
    arr + 2     arr - 2     arr * 2     arr / 2

Other operations:
    np.sqrt(arr)    Square-root
    np.exp(arr)     Exponential
    np.sin(arr)     Sinosuidal
    np.log(arr)     Logarithm
    
